    <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
      <head>Biographical History</head>
      <p>
                    Kendall Taylor was an American art historian and biographer of American Social Realist painter Philip Evergood.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
      <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
      <p>The <emph render="bold">Kendall Taylor Collection relating to Philip Evergood</emph> is focused on Philip Evergood (1901-1973), an American social realist painter who was active from the 1930s through the 1960s.
  The collection is divided into two sections.</p><p>The <emph render="bold">Philip Evergood</emph> series contains original research material relating to Evergood and consists of correspondence, photographs, exhibition catalogs, some of Evergood's writings, and memorabilia.   The <emph render="bold">Kendall Taylor</emph> series contains the papers of Kendall Taylor, his biographer, comprising drafts and research notes relating to her work on Evergood.</p>
    </scopecontent>
    <arrangement encodinganalog="351$a">
      <head>Arrangement of the Collection</head>
      <p>Material is arranged alphabetically, by name, type or title as appropriate.</p>
    </arrangement>
    <relatedmaterial encodinganalog="544 1">
      <head>Related Material</head>
      <p>A small amount of additional Evergood material may be found in the <extref href="../e/evergood_p.htm">Philip Evergood Papers</extref>.</p>
    </relatedmaterial>
